INSERT INTO `artists` VALUES (2,'Mo Rayon','morayon','df3ce-morayon.png','b1679-morays.png','<p>\n	Growing up north in israel, kind of secluded, running in the forests and the valleys beatboxing in school, Mo started flirting with music in early 2008, being influenced by all kinds of dozed off sounds,experimental music, and romanticism he has sharpend his edge over the years and began producing a more refined version of his unique take on hip hop.</p>\n<p>\n	Most recently joining raw tapes, <span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".1n0.$mid=11408623241686=2a07b275df1c96ad959.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">he began collaboration with different members of the crew, creating various tracks and EPs, all with his unique abstract touch &amp; hazey vocals</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/morayon','','','https://www.facebook.com/morayon',''),(3,'Playdead','playdead','c4fb7-playdead.png','5d623-playdread.png','<p>\n	Playdead is out of the grave and back in the game.</p>\n<p>\n	This engimatic and mystic duo rocks and bangs with all hands moving.</p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','','','','https://www.facebook.com/playdeadRAWTAPES',''),(4,'Guadaloop / Rejoicer','guada','a50c3-rejguad.png','db86e-rej.png','<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".2v.$mid=11408613071782=2be31ce5f0489d8b450.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">Yuval Havkin aka Rejoicer is one of Tel Aviv&rsquo;s busiest producers and founder of the Raw Tapes label, home to Israel&rsquo;s own beat movement. </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".2v.$mid=11408613071782=2be31ce5f0489d8b450.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">He was born in London and moved to Tel Aviv at the age of 5. He began collecting vinyl at the age of 14, and started his way in the music world as a Jungle/Drum&amp;Bass artist in 2006. He later moved on to hip hop, and produced beat tapes under the Guadaloop moniker.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".2v.$mid=11408613071782=2be31ce5f0489d8b450.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">After finding a crew of like minded beat makers from around the city, Rejoicer founded the Raw Tapes Label in 2009. </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".2v.$mid=11408613071782=2be31ce5f0489d8b450.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">Since then he released more then 20 albums under all different aliases. In 2011 Rejoicer started the band Buttering Trio with KerenDun and Beno Hendler and released Toast LP. the trio played shows with Oh No &amp; DJ Romes, Black Milk, Peanut Butter Wolf, Hudson Mohawke and more. He has collaborated with Free The Robots, Dudley Perkins &amp; Georgia Anne Muldrow, Bajka, Balkan Beat Box, Ester Rada, Cohenbeats and many more, and continues to be one of Tel Aviv&rsquo;s most interesting artists</span></span></p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/rejoicer','','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Rejoicer/112958008718165',''),(5,'KerenDun','kerendun','dc899-kerendun.png','acb64-kd.png','<p>\n	When not co-producing and singing for Buttering trio, Kerendun makes beats. And shes damn good at it too.</p>\n<p>\n	We&#39;re not quite sure where she gets her influences from, But it seems like a head on collision of african rhytmes with jazzy electronics, Lots of precussion and soft synths. sounds like a blessing.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/kerendun','','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/KerenDun/624735250910497',''),(6,'Sinez','sinez','18ee7-sinez.png','7f53f-dubzsinez.png','<p>\n	A contemporery hip-hop producer, Sinez brings forth an innovative mixture of new and old notions of hip-hop.</p>\n<p>\n	While mostly influenced by Madlib and Jay Dilla, Sinez incorporates a variety of different flavors in underground music, such as reggae, jungle, techno, and bass music in general.</p>\n<p>\n	With grooves set on the ninties vibes and booming compressed synth bass, Sinez tierlessly works on his vision for the continuity of hip hop.</p>\n','','','','',''),(7,'L.B.T','LBT','6fee2-lbt.png','','<p>\n	Live Beat Tapes is a new concept that revolves around a collection of talents devoting themselves to the making of one long track.<br />\n	The basic idea is building original beats with mostly acoustic instruments. A very collective way of thinking and the use of friendship and sharing among the music scene in Israel results in one of the freshest sounds around.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/live-beat-tapes','https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCspUrCfb7quRgf53vZ4KEuA','','https://www.facebook.com/livebeattapes',''),(8,'Luqman','luqman','aad4a-luqman.png','3011f-luq.png','<p>\n	A jazz guitarist coming from a musical background of mostly punk and jazz - what could go wrong?</p>\n<p>\n	Coming across J Dilla and Madlib beats at some point in his life made him drop the guitar and pick up some drum pads, bang some hot beats and rejuvinate our ear sets.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/the_luqman','','','https://www.facebook.com/Luqmanbeats','e0105-hp_luqman.png'),(9,'CohenBeats','cohen','a36a7-cohen.png','1b7b9-cohen.png','<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".1n0.$mid=11408619112360=20f787ea71fb29b2150.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">Michael Cohen, AKA Cohenbeats, started his musical career at 17, rapping and making beats as part of the local Israeli Hip Hop trio Cohen@Mushon. Influenced by the Native Tongue movement, the band introduced a new style of Tel Aviv hip hop, and achieved mainstream success with 2 albums, extensive tours and even a radio smash hit.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".1n0.$mid=11408619112360=20f787ea71fb29b2150.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">In 2008 Cohen took part in the Red Bull Music Academy in Barcelona. This experience first exposed him to the worldwide beat movement and connected him with people like Dorian Concept, Teebs and Fatima. Cohen began developing his production style and making instrumental Hip Hop. in 2011, Cohen@Mushon decided to take a hiatus, and Cohen relocated to LA, where he connected with the local scene, working with local talents like Samiyam, Mndsgn, Shafiq Husayn and Open Mike Eagle</span></span><span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".1n0.$mid=11408619112360=20f787ea71fb29b2150.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".1n0.$mid=11408619112360=20f787ea71fb29b2150.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">Still feeling a deep bond to his homeland and a will to present a unique sound, he released Milk &amp; Honey Vol.1, an instrumental beat album based solely on Israeli samples, via the Tel Aviv Raw Tapes label. He also teamed up with rapper/producer Jeremiah Jae, for a joint EP called pennies (released 2014 on YellowMask).</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".1n0.$mid=11408619112360=20f787ea71fb29b2150.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">in 2014, Cohen returned to his hometown of Tel Aviv. He released &ldquo;Thank You Los Angeles&rdquo;, a free beat tape containing his best work from his time in LA, and also released a solo rap EP called rap, featuring some beats from his LA friends. He is currently working on Milk &amp; Honey Vol. 2 and plotting his return to the city of angels&hellip;</span></span></p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/cohenbeatsaredope','http://cohenraps.bandcamp.com/','','https://www.facebook.com/cohenbeatsaredope','db064-hp_cohenbeats.png'),(10,'Mad Steve','madsteve','b6ba6-madsteve.png','','<p>\n	This french monster dosen&#39;t really care about anything but beats and 70s electronic space synths.</p>\n<p>\n	Taking cold, ambient synthslines and cutting them into soulful - swinging beats, is what we call the perfection in imperfections.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/mad-steve','http://madaya.bandcamp.com/','','',''),(11,'Jengo','jengo','5c249-jengo.png','','','','','','https://www.facebook.com/ohjengo',''),(12,'Nomok','Nomok','89ce6-nomok.png','03504-nom.png','<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".21.$mid=11408613208895=2ee9b1bcf5e61fb7508.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">A pianist at heart with a straight-ahead jazz facade, Nomok took a turn for the worse and will now surely throw you off guard with his unexpected movements and slick beats</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".21.$&lt;1408611529476=23837713681-1125228158@mail=1projektitan=1com&gt;.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">In his debut EP Nomok nails blazing, passionate melodies on top of earthly, organic grooves, and pretty much reminded us the foundation of raw tapes</span></span><span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".21.$&lt;1408611529476=23837713681-1125228158@mail=1projektitan=1com&gt;.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">. </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span class=\"_5yl5\" data-reactid=\".21.$&lt;1408611529476=23837713681-1125228158@mail=1projektitan=1com&gt;.2:0.0.0.0.0\"><span class=\"null\">His extensive work in L.B.T is also astonishing, playing keys, producing and recording alot of the sessions.</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	&nbsp;</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/nomok','','','https://www.facebook.com/n0m0k','45c43-hp_nomok.png'),(13,'Beno','beno','2e35b-beno.png','','<p>\n	Beno, the godfather of bass guitar, and the head of the spear which is called L.B.T, is a long time producer and a friend.</p>\n<p>\n	While not busy in the studio, he&#39;s out playing gigs with the likes of Balkan Beat Box and Berry Saharoff</p>\n<p>\n	When producing by himself he explores various tempos and grooves, sounding unearthly and unique.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/beno-hendler-1','','','',''),(14,'Buttering Trio','bt3','6c42c-buttering.png','27d63-btt.png','<p>\n	This particular Berlin/Tel Aviv connection crafts densely layered and sophisticated nu soul not a million miles away from Quadron, Georgia Anne Muldrow or Little Dragon. At the same time, these aural treats are not for the faint of heart: KerenDun, Rejoicer (a. o. producer of Bajka) and bassist Beno Hendler (<span class=\"text_exposed_show\">Balkan Beat Box) love to lace their sound with sharp synth bass, progressive chords and off-kilter, yet never off-key, beats and vox for a challenging sonic journey inspired by the grandmaster of all things &ldquo;out there,&ldquo; Frank Zappa. So, listen closely &hellip; or you might miss some of the tricky snippets thrown into the mix!</span></p>\n','','','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Buttering-Trio/271205742901210','a2df9-hp_buttering.png'),(15,'Citizen Kane','CK','eb80b-citizenkane.png','7d527-ck.png','<p>\n	Perfectionism is not a bad thing</p>\n<p>\n	Ranging from lo-fi bangers to up tempo, complex 808 rhytmes, Kane&#39;s attention to smallest details whether in the synth he chooses, the unique approach to drum programming and the overall mix makes other producers realise they have to work harder on thier beats.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/citizen-kane','','','',''),(16,'DubZ','dubz','aa4c2-dubz.png','d5f9d-dubzsinez.png','','https://soundcloud.com/gotdubz','','','https://www.facebook.com/dubznthangz',''),(17,'Galo','Galo','4632f-galo.png','a5a31-galo.png','<p>\n	Galo is a well roasted figure on and around the decks, with legally binding vibes and the ill behavior.</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/dj-galo-d','','','https://www.facebook.com/galothedj','2d20a-hp_galo.png'),(18,'Plusga','plusga','89093-plusga.png','0cd0c-plus.png','','https://soundcloud.com/plusga','','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Plusga/503249436356141','53e07-hp_plusga.png'),(19,'Radixx','radixx','8d568-radixx.png','','','https://soundcloud.com/radixxx','','','',''),(20,'Mesh','mesh','dc5aa-mesh.png','0931c-mesh.png','','','','','','f3ef3-hp_mesh.png'),(22,'Table Knights','','1dcb7-untitled-3.png','','','','','','',''),(23,'Sol Monk','SolMonk','50851-so-l22.png','','','','','','',''),(24,'Yudko','Yudko','b7a2c-judko.png','','<p>\n	Yudkoyudkoyudkoyudko</p>\n','https://soundcloud.com/yudko','','','',''),(25,'Kalimist','Kalimist','0ef04-kali.png','08bb1-kali2.png','','https://soundcloud.com/kalimist','','','','');
