INSERT INTO `releases` VALUES (3,3,'The Hipster Move','793455085','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/the-hipster-move','','<p>\n	<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-style: italic; line-height: 14.882790565490723px;\">This mysterious mask wearing duo - PlayDead - made the album using drum machines, a variety of synths and a very limited vocabulary, to produce ill, alienated beat based music.&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-style: italic; line-height: 14.882790565490723px; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" />\n	<br style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-style: italic; line-height: 14.882790565490723px; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" />\n	<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-style: italic; line-height: 14.882790565490723px;\">These pieces represent a wider spectrum of their bizarre world and a continuum to their last EP. It&#39;s only natural then, that &quot;The Hipster Move&quot; will be a groove fit for your home as well as for the club.</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px;\">Music by PlayDead (Rejoicer &amp; Shuz)&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px;\">Mastering - Asaf Shay&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" />\n	<br style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" />\n	<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px;\">Design by Kip (Broken Fingaz)&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" />\n	<br style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\" />\n	<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; line-height: 14.882790565490723px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne Green</span></span></span></p>\n','00428-playdead_hipster_web_1000.jpg','2014-03-27 12:00:00','thehipstermove',NULL),(4,12,'Puzzles Vol. 2','837635269','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/puzzles-vol-2','','<p>\n	Unlike most of our releases that focus on one artist, the Puzzles series compiles music from many different artists within the Raw Tapes household. We tried to capture the current collective soundscape, homogeneous yet diverse, in 9 beats.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Mastering by Asaf Shay </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Design by Jengo </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne Green tags</span></span></p>\n','e577d-puzlles2.jpg','2014-03-08 12:00:00','puzzles2',NULL),(5,2,'The Feels ','4147912050','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/the-feels','','<p>\n	Mo Rayon is a sensitive dude. In this second album, the erratic maestro crafted 9 syrupy, luscious beats as a suitable ground for his peculiar singing and rapping, revealing his kaleidoscope world of emotions. To his words, &quot;Back when I had the feels, I knew it must be for reals&quot;.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced and mixed by Mo Rayon</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Additional Mix by Nomok </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastered by Asaf Shay</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Always in charge - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','a97ec-the-feels.jpg','2013-12-28 12:00:00','thefeels',NULL),(6,4,'Åfarica','2793818407','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/farica','','<p>\n	After a long hiatus, Guadaloop comes back from the gutter to bring us this trip of an album. Continuing the Indian samples based album concept, Guadaloop now travels to the poignant land of Africa, twisting and mutating those indigenous sounds into what Guadaloop knows how to do best; weird Hip Hop beats. This almost seems too natural for this guy, who has always had a liaison with tribal rhythms. Guadaloop translates the classic rhythms and sounds of Africa into a modern celebration of ethnic ambience.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Beats by Guadaloop </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering - Asaf Shay</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design - Jengo </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green Big </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Thanks goes to - Beno Hendler, Nomok, Mo Rayon, Luqman, KerenDun, Asaf, LBT, Shlomo Bar, Eyal Talmudi, DJ Mesh, The Doctor, Keves (Tiny Fingers), Kip</span></span></p>\n','a39d8-cover.jpg','2013-11-16 12:00:00','afarica',NULL),(7,5,'Shakin\' The Tips','3777759990',' http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/shakin-the-tips','','<p>\n	&quot;Something strange is coming your way&quot;</p>\n<p>\n	There&#39;s a strong energy flow in KerenDun&#39;s music - creating a very fluid world and a lucid-dream like feeling. Keren&#39;s second installment on RT is a clear and natural musical evolution. After recording in the last year 2 studio albums with Buttering Trio and preforming live dozens of shows with her own music, she releases this mesmerizing 4 tracks album.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Written, Produced and Mixed by KerenDun</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Track 3 Produced with Yudko</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Asaf Shay</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Always in charge - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','9fa35-shaking-the-tips.jpg','2013-10-31 12:00:00','shakin',NULL),(8,4,'Stay Low','2772926934','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/stay-low','','<p>\n	Summer. Degrees rise to over 25 C and the best place to cool off is in the air conditioned studio. Wary of being outside for too long, cats like A7 and Guadaloop end up having longer sessions than ever, propelling them to record as much music as possible. Thus comes to you &quot;Stay Low&quot;, the 2nd Raw Tapes X A7 collab, continuing the 1st one with Plusga, &quot;Blasphemy&quot;. This time A7 picks 4 beats by Guadaloop, which were intended for the upcoming Guadaloop in Africa album and rips them with his usual colorful, tenacious lyrics. Having DJ Mesh, Beno and Nomok as frequent guests in the studio contributed even more to the mood and helped polish this sleek 4 track release.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Vox &#39;n&#39; Lyrics by A7 aka Rebel Sun </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Beats by Guadaloop </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Cuts by DJ Mesh </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Bass (on tracks 2+3) by Beno Hendler </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Rhodes (on tracks 2+3) by Nomok </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Asaf Shay @ Kicha Studios</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Always in charge - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','23197-cover.jpg','2013-09-09 12:00:00','staylow',NULL),(9,12,'Blind Kick','1729465966','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/blind-kick-ep','','<p>\n	In this short EP Nomok nails blazing, passionate melodies on top of earthly, organic grooves and pretty much reminds us the foundation of Raw Tapes.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced and Mixed by Nomok</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Asaf Shai</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','60992-blind-kick.jpg','2013-06-28 12:00:00','blindkick',NULL),(10,8,'Altered Thinking','2613988086','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/luqman-altered-thinking','','<p>\n	We are pleased to announce Luqman&#39;s debut EP - Altered Thinking. A jazz guitarist, coming from a musical background of punk and jazz, Luqman came across some Dilla and Madlib beats which made him drop the strings and pick up the drum pads. 1 year later, and this 21 year young cat is grasping the beat movement by the balls. As a guitarist Luqman was always dependant on his fellow band members to create a whole song and be able to fully implement his visions - but now he&#39;s calling the shots. And thank god he does. Some jazzy, 8-bit chords, some phat saw waves, drums so raw they almost sound acoustic.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All tracks produced and mixed by Luqman</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">except track 7 produced by Luq@dasinez</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art &amp; Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Photograph by Opal Kravchuk</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer: Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green.</span></span></p>\n','33d1a-cover.jpg','2011-11-19 12:00:00','altered',NULL),(11,4,'Recollection','1638530725','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/recollection','','<p>\n	Recollection is the pathway to self-reflection. The explaining of memories as in form of &quot;talking to one&#39;s self&quot;. Searching deep into life&#39;s quiet moments. To find joy gained by experience. Rejoicer has been busy. For the past year he has produced countless MCs, singers and musicians, and finally the time has come for his own debut album: Recollection - a path into his own beat-making approach. Dive. Deep.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced and Mixed by Rejoicer @ RJ Studios, TLV 2013</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Vox and Lyrics on tracks 2, 10 - Bajka</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">5 - KerenDun</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">9 - Rotem Or</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Keyz (Fender Rhodes, Moog, Juno 60, Roland SH 10) on tracks 1, 6, 7, 10, 11 by Nomok</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Bass on racks 1, 2, 11 by Beno</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Drums on track 8 by Roy Chen</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering - Asaf Shay @ Kicha Studios</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art by Kip @Broken Fingaz</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','e0803-recollection.jpg','2013-05-27 12:00:00','recollection',NULL),(12,4,'Yuka - Calo Wood vol. 1','4153930201','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/yuka-calo-wood-vol-1','','<p>\n	Rejoicer and Eyal Talmudi go on a jazzy trip with Yuka, in the first Calo Wood session.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Vox + Lyrics + Yukalele by Yuka</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All Instruments by Eyal Talmudi &amp; Rejoicer</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced by Calo Wood (Eyal Talmudi &amp; Rejoicer)</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Bass on Track 8 by Beno Hendler</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mixed by Rejoicer @ RJ Studios, Tel Aviv</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Marko Gurken @ Kicha Studios</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green + Udi Barak</span></span></p>\n','cae04-calo.jpg','2013-05-01 12:00:00','Yuka',NULL),(13,10,'Street Hype EP','1246554660','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/mad-steve-rejoicer-street-hype-ep','','<p>\n	4 booming beats these two stoners made back in December 09, all wrapped up and ready for you to click the download button.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Mixed and mastered @ Raw Tapes Studio by MS+RJ</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"font-size:10px;\"><span style=\"color:#696969;\">Always in charge - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','e1c3e-streethype.jpg','2010-06-05 12:00:00','streethype',NULL),(14,2,'Astral Walks Forever','1977972707','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/astral-walks-forever','','<p>\n	Introducing Mo Rayon in a debut album of voodoo love. 4 spaced out beats that will make you feel like your&#39;e drowning in a pink ocean of juicy lust, lost in a sticky haze of reverbed emotions.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All beats produced and mixed by Mo Rayon</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color: rgb(105, 105, 105); font-size: 10px;\">Mastering by Isaac Gr&aacute; Finley</span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art and Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer: Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','797b0-mo-astral.jpg','2013-04-16 12:00:00','astral',NULL),(15,8,'Synthesizer Colossus','2498268179','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/synthesizer-colossus','','<p>\n	A second release by Luqman, Synthesizer Colossus explores the competence of crude synthesized sound waves. The young hooligan slaps in the face of over-layering, creating a world of minimal grooves and crispy, clear sounds, keeping it more raw than it ever was.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All beats produced by Luqman</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Kalimist</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art and Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Photograph by Lemuel Barbour</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer: Osbourne Green</span></span></p>\n','4a4ca-luqman.jpg','2013-03-30 12:00:00','synthesizerc',NULL),(16,18,'Beat Batch #2','99268154','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/plusga-beat-batch-2','','<p>\n	Another beat batch by the world famous Plusga. Straight beats.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Beats by Plusga</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Always in Charge - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','6919d-blob.png','2010-07-10 12:00:00','beatbatch2',NULL),(17,14,'Party Bear EP','1926237517','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/buttering-trio-party-bear-ep','','<p>\n	Buttering Trio is consisting of KerenDun, Rejoicer and GymBass. After knowing each other for more then 10 years they magically met again in Kreuzberg, Berlin, and started jamming together. &quot;Party Bear EP&quot; is the result of their co-meditation and love for music. SPREAD THE LOVE</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Written and produced by Rejoicer, KerenDun and GymBass</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Vocals by KerenDun and GymBass</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Bass by GymBass</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Recording and Mixing by Rejoicer @ Buttering Trio Studio, WrangelStr. 666, Berlin</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork and design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','b5639-partybearf.jpg','2011-09-22 12:00:00','partybear',NULL),(18,14,'Toast','2381663537','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/toast','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/toast/id883919551','<p>\n	&quot;Toast&quot; is the debut LP by Buttering Trio, consisting of beats by KerenDun, Rejoicer and Beno, and is the result of the cooperation of the three during the past year, collaborating with the best musicians around. The beats came to life in three different studios - Wrangelstr. 666 Studio Berlin, Spaceship Studio Kibbutz Dunietz and Kicha Studios Tel Aviv, making the album a kind of a schizophrenic new-school romantic child. MAKE FALAFEL NOT WAR.</p>\n<p>\n	&quot;Toast sublimely combines ballads and beats in a manner that redefines trip-hop: deep, melancholic tunes accompanied by a groove that lies on the aesthetics of Dilla&quot; Shuzin, 3421</p>\n<p>\n	Get the full experience: Butteringtrio.com</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Music by Buttering Trio (KerenDun, Beno, Rejoicer)</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Lyrics by KerenDun</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">&quot;Ganja Man&quot; written by GYMBass (Gal Yaron Meirson)</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Additional Lyrics on &quot;Falafel&quot; by Maya Dunietz, Beno Hendler</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Additional Vocals on &quot;Ganja Man&quot; - Adir The Doctor Dadia</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Keyz on &quot;Ibiza&quot; and &quot;Mean To Me&quot; by Asaf Talmudi</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Keyz on &quot;Tired Love&quot; by Maya Dunietz</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Keyz on &quot;Berliner&quot; by Amit Alcalai</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Bass on &quot;Berliner&quot; by GYMBass</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Recording Engineer on tracks 1,2,3,8,10 - Adir Dadia, Asaf Shay, Marko Gurkan</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Marko Gurkan @ Kicha Studios , TLV</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art and Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Special thanks - Maya Dunietz, Arline Kremerman, Noam Havkin, DJ Werd, Yaki and Esti Dunietz, Dana Dunietz, Don Juan, The Doctor, Eyal Talmudi, Kip tags</span></span></p>\n','598dd-cover.jpg','2013-02-09 12:00:00','toast',NULL),(19,15,'Puzzles Vol. 1','3088406532','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/puzzles','','<p>\n	3 years ago we have put out a CD compiling beats from all the Raw Tapes beat makers and producers. It was our 2nd release ever and we were very proud of it, putting out lots of singles, albums, EPs and mixtapes since. We have always believed that Raw Tapes is merely the sum of its artists, thus felt a need for another compilation. So here it is, an 11 track album by the 11 beat makers and producers you have loved every single month for the past couple of years.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Music by Plusga, KerenDun, CohenBeats, Beno Hendler, Luqman Rejoicer//Guadaloop, Mad Steve, Citizen Kane, Sinez &amp; Radixx</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Jonathan Jacobi</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art and Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','0cbda-puzzles2.jpg','2013-01-31 12:00:00','puzzles',NULL),(20,9,'Milk & Honey','135326595','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/milk-and-honey','','<p>\n	Cohenbeats has been a long time friend and one of the best beat makers we know. It was only a matter of time until he would&#39;ve released an album on Raw Tapes... Even though Cohenbeats (also one half of the rap group Cohen@Mushon) has always had a soft spot for Israeli samples, this time he focused on 25 of his favorite beats sampled only from Israeli records from the 60&#39;s up to the 80&#39;s, 2 beats from Israeli related samples and many skits of Israeli people speaking half ass English. We even went far enough to feature Hebrew writings on the cover, if you ever wondered what it looked like... We figured since all we hear in the news is political related, we needed someone to show us another side of the middle east. So there you go, 27 nose punching, throat grabbing, heart moving beats.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All tracks produced and mixed by Cohenbeats</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Additional mixing by Ori Shochat</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastered by Josh Cramer at the Ranch, NYC</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Thanks to all the friends who let me roam through their record collection: DJ Hectik, Jonathan &ldquo;Shuali&rdquo; Sharoni, Ofer Schoolmaster, Dan Farkas, Arale Kaminski, Yair Niko, Mike Mushon.</span></span></p>\n','b4ddb-milk.jpg','2012-12-15 12:00:00','Milknhoney',NULL),(21,19,'Honey Roast','3505644391','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/honey-roast','','<p>\n	The cold days had Radixx piling up with stacks of advils and oranges. We figure this combination is the catalyst for this epic rollercoaster of a beat, packing enough heat for the winter that&#39;s upon us. A journey into one&rsquo;s madness. This is a single from Radixx&rsquo;s upcoming album, currently titled Rain Bounxx.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All music written &amp; produced by Radixx</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by AWAZ, Los Angeles, California</span></span></p>\n','18c0b-roast.jpg','2012-11-30 12:00:00','honeyroast',NULL),(22,6,'Luckhour','1946572265','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/luckhour','','<p>\n	You probably want to hear the whole story behind this 5 track album, so here it is, digital black on white - DJ Werd invited the some of the Raw Tapes crew - Rejoicer, Plusga and Dubz to play for 2 nights, in Berlin and in Dresden. The whole gang (plus Soundpeices who also joined in) spent a week at Werd&#39;s studio in Luckauer Strasse, Berlin. Vibing together in the studio, these 5 beats were made.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">*track 1 - Produced by Plusga, Sinez and Rejoicer. Mixed by Plusga</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">*track 2 - Produced by Open SRC (Rejoicer and Dubz). Scratches by DJ Werd. Mixed by Rejoicer</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">*track 3 - Produced and Mixed by Rejoicer</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">*track 4 - Produced by Sines. Mixed by Plusga. *track 5 - Produced by Sinez and DJ Werd. Mixed by Plusga</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','909ae-luck.jpg','2011-01-28 12:00:00','luckhour',NULL),(23,19,'Black Keys (Single)','3731779542','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/radixx-black-keys-single','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/radixx-black-keys-single','<p>\n	This is a single from the upcoming Radixx EP, including a free Tweet remix. EP should be released in the next few weeks.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">music by Radixx</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork by Jengo</span></span></p>\n','2a71c-blackkeys.jpg','2010-10-16 12:00:00','blackeys',NULL),(24,15,'B.A.B.O.B','3997643402','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/citizen-kane-b-a-b-o-b','','<p>\n	Back in 2010, this album was actually supposed to be a mere beat tape consisting of about 8 beats, just to let the people listen to some music by the Citizen. But fact is, Kane is one hell of a perfectionist. Not a single frequency slips his ears, not a single hit slips the groove. This means deadline postponing, but this ultimately means one hell of an album, debut, for Citizen Kane. Please help yourself with some space synths &amp; soulful grooves.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced and Mixed by Citizen Kane</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','46f7a-babob.jpg','2011-10-15 12:00:00','babob',NULL),(25,16,'Wood','2389175030','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/open-src-wood','','<p>\n	After working together as a duo for the last 4 years, Rejoicer and Sinez had decided to finally put together an album consisting of their best beats as Open SRC. A lot of beats were mere sketches or unfinished, mostly because, all though close friends, they both have a different mindset and attitude. That forced them to find common grounds, which at points seemed to be too experimental or, on the other hand, too basic (for them). Their debute album, &quot;Wood&quot;, tries to unite those beats which represent the perfect collision between the two minds, creating soulful &amp; energetic beats, which are simply on-point.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Arranged and Mixed by Open SRC (Rejoicer and Sinez) @ Raw Tapes Studio, 2010</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">*Except Tracks 1,3,6,9 - @ Rejoicer Studio, 2009|2010</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Artwork and Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n','44a88-wood.jpg','2011-06-15 12:00:00','wood',NULL),(26,13,'Game Over','2163043541','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/game-over','','<p>\n	This is Beno&#39;s debut album - and it&#39;s definitely not the one you&#39;d expect it to be. After playing for ethnic rock bands, producing ska bands and working with left field producers, Beno has finally came up with his solo beat album in which he put all of his previous work aside to make way for a new sound. Being the multi-color person he is, Beno took this album to a place that was new to him - the dance floor. On this album Beno tried to stick to the 4/4 pattern and hard sounds, and eventually came up with this 7 track banger-only, heavyweight, grimey release. WATCH OUT</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Beats and Mix by Beno</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Jonathan Jacobi @ FireHouse, Tel Aviv</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer : Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n','dfbb8-gameover.jpg','2012-09-30 12:00:00','gameover',NULL),(27,5,'Subconscious Leak','291522618','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/subconscious-leak','','<p>\n	Subconscious Leak is KerenDun&#39;s debut album, taking you on a sweet, psychedelic journey of rhythms and sounds. Throughout the album you will find heavy, precise percussion, vintage synthesizer sounds and vocals that sneak up and act just as another instrument, and as a reminder of the human factor. &quot;This is my inevitable subconscious spill, as it is represented by instrumental beats&quot;.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Beats and Vox by KerenDun</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mixed by KerenDun &amp; Rejoicer @ Buttering Trio Studio, Wrangel Str. 666, Berlin</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Marko Gurkan @Kicha Studios, TLV</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art and Design by Jengo</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer - Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Special thanks go to Ditta, Revital, Miri, Michal &amp; Esti for womanly presence And to Ori Shochat for the supernatural help.</span></span></p>\n','c52b3-sub.jpg','2012-09-25 12:00:00','SubconsciousLeak',NULL),(28,6,'Yelloweed','1228789185','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/yelloweed','','<p>\n	This album is about a collaboration of musical agendas. It&#39;s an unfiltered raw product of how we reflect on the changes in style and texture that this music has been going through. Luqman El Hakim, Dubz &amp; Rejoicer met in two consecutive saturdays of Februrary, 2012 and crafted this 6 piece album.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">All tracks produced by Rejoicer, DubZ &amp; Luqman&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mixed by Rejoicer @ SpaceShip studio&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Art &amp; design by Jengo&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\">\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastering by Kalimist</span></span></p>\n','f40f6-yelloweed.jpg','2012-07-07 12:00:00','yelloweed',NULL),(29,13,'Galaxy Cross ','3102848041','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/identical-testicle-galaxy-cross','','<p>\n	Smoking the best weed, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, hasn&#39;t slowed down Beno and Rejoicer a bit - they fire up beats by the minute. One would think that making so many beats in such a short period of time results in a monotonous plethora but on the contrary - many different styles, different BPMs, using many tools of trade such as Moog, African and Swiss percussion, guitars and bass guitars, Ableton Live, Harps, all sorts of old and obscure synthesizers - just to name a few! An omnicultural celebration of beats.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced by: Beno Hendler and Rejoicer </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mixed by Asaf Shay &amp; Identical Testicle @ Kicha </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Keys on &quot;10 G&quot; by Piloni </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Vox and vibes on &quot;Dragons&quot; by KerenDun </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Harp on &quot;Say Wow&quot; by Renana Hendler Ne&#39;eman </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Mastered by: Marko Gurcan @ Kicha </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Photography by: Haidi Motola </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Design by: Jengo </span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Executive Producer: Osbourne &quot;Ease&quot; Green&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n','d18b2-galaxy.jpg','2012-06-28 12:00:00','galaxycross',NULL),(31,4,'Just The Truth','1899629255','http://rawtapes.bandcamp.com/album/bajka-just-the-truth','','<p>\n	Bajka is the people&#39;s voice, searching for the truth in a confusing reality where people don&#39;t ask right questions but want the right answers. But let&#39;s take it about 365 days ago (2011...) - Rejoicer moves to Berlin to start a new life, little does he know he is about to meet Bajka, a strong woman with an even stronger voice who is on the look out for fresh producers. 2 minutes is all it took for both to realize it was a heaven made match, Rejoicer&#39;s ambient yet powerfull synths and Bajka&#39;s mesmerizing, almost hypnotic voice, half rapping half preaching for a bright new world, fit together perfectly, pushing the boundaries of soul music into new soundscapes.</p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Vox by Bajka</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\"font-size:10px;\">Produced, Recorded and Mixed by Rejoicer @ LuckHour Studios, Berlin</span></span></p>\n<p>\n	<span style=\"color:#696969;\"><span style=\